Description: Kickfire is an analytic database appliance manufacturer for the MySQL data warehouse market.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Kickfire makes an analytic appliance for the MySQL data warehouse market. With 11 million active installations, MySQL is the world's most popular open source database and its adoption is accelerating. As the amount of data stored in MySQL grows, so too does the requirement to analyze this data for business decision making. However, the technologies required for data warehousing and high-performance query and reporting within the leading proprietary databases such as Oracle and SQL Server don't exist in MySQL. Kickfire has the answer. By combining hardware and software innovations with the ease-of-use of the MySQL open source database, Kickfire brings to market an analytic appliance with unheard of performance, simplicity, and economics. At the core of every Kickfire appliance is a new SQL chip that radically alters the economics of query processing by packing the power of 10s of CPUs into a single chip. Just as NVIDIA moved graphics processing from software to hardware, Kickfire has done the same for database operations. This disruptive innovation facilitates tremendous improvements in speed and reductions in cost and power. With Kickfire, the MySQL data warehouse market now has a fully functional, load-and-go analytic appliance that rivals any of the proprietary database appliances or specialized analytic databases in the world. And there is no expensive hardware buildout or complex tuning required. Kickfire was founded in 2006 by Raj Cherabuddi and Joseph Chamdani, two proven entrepreneurs with more than 50 issued patents. Prior to Kickfire, they founded Sanera Systems, a startup that focused on mission-critical, high-performance SAN switches. Sanera was successfully acquired by McDATA, a public company with $800M in annual revenues, and is now part of Brocade. Backed by blue chip investors Accel Partners, Greylock Partners, Mayfield Fund and Pinnacle Ventures, Kickfire is headquartered in Santa Clara, California.
Top 5 Investors: Accel, Greylock, 3i Group, Mayfield Fund, Pinnacle Ventures

Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Our Lady of Fatima Hospital in North Providence, Rhode Island, is home to the St. Joseph School of Nursing, which offers compassionate and dedicated students the opportunity to pursue a three-year Nursing diploma. While the St. Joseph School is Catholic, it does not require its students to share the same faith commitment, as it invites students from all religious backgrounds to attend. To support you during your training, St. Joseph’s faculty offers plenty of student services, like career guidance and counseling. You can also enhance your education by taking advantage of the learning resources available to you, including the health sciences library, nursing arts laboratory and audiovisual laboratory. You can make the most out of your college life by participating in St. Joseph’s many health fairs and wellness initiatives, designed to aid the local North Providence community. Since the nursing program requires students to complete coursework in the social, physical and health sciences, St. Joseph allows its students to transfer credits from or enroll in courses offered at the Community College of Rhode Island and Rhode Island College. Applicants who have graduated high school or hold a GED and are at least 18 years old will be considered for enrollment. Additional admissions requirements include letters of recommendation, a personal essay and computer competence. St. Joseph is authorized to offer financial aid to qualifying students who file a FAFSA.

Description: Dlandstudio is an interdisciplinary design firm.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: dlandstudio is an interdisciplinary design firm founded in 2005 by Susannah C. Drake. Prior to starting an independent practice, Susannah worked for architects and landscape architects in New York, Cape Cod, New Hampshire, Wyoming and San Francisco. Exposure to diverse ecosystems, population densities, and scales of operation enriched her vision of what makes places truly special.  The firm provides an integrated approach to planning, programming and design. As leader and collaborator on large teams that include architects, artists, landscape architects, planners, and engineers, dlandstudio helps enrich team consideration of expressions of landscape meaning while maintaining focus on project goals throughout the development process. The firm is committed to creating projects with a strong conceptual basis drawn from an understanding of the place, the client, the program, and appropriate construction techniques. Their goal is to create beautifully designed, ecologically intelligent, and well executed projects that work well at the large scale and are executed in rigorous detail. Since its establishment, dlandstudio has grown to include both national and international projects. Recent works include the Gowanus Canal Sponge Park™, a public open space system designed to absorb and remediate stormwater, the Brooklyn Bridge Pop-up Park, a temporary waterfront open space that attracted almost two hundred thousand visitors over thirteen weeks of operation in 2008, and the security for the New York City Police Department headquarters in Lower Manhattan. dlandstudio’s current international work includes the Raising Malawi Academy for Girls outside of Lilongwe, Malawi and the design of a 1200 acre public park and resort development in Abuja, Nigeria. The firm’s Brooklyn Queens Expressway trench study and Gowanus Canal Sponge Park™ project are the recipients of numerous awards from the American Institute of Architecture and American Society of Landscape Architects.

Description: The Julie Moore Real Estate Team is committed to achieving timely results.
Full Description: The Julie Moore Real Estate Team is committed to achieving timely results for our clients with a high standard of professionalism and integrity. Our communication skills coupled with extensive real estate knowledge ensures your needs will be carried out professionally, efficiently and personally.  My assistant, Lindsay Oltrogge, and I are an energetic, highly driven, residential real estate team. We strive every day to create a smooth transaction for each client with frequent communication, an individualized game plan and specific approach. We work hard to educate each client about every step of the home selling and buying process. For the 4th year in a row, the Julie Moore Real Estate Team has finished in the top 3% of all realtors in Des Moines, selling over 30 million in residential real estate. We currently sell, on average, one home per week. Approximately 90% of our business comes from referrals. Our clients range first time home buyers to executive relocations. We also list and sell downtown lofts, acreages, townhomes, and foreclosures. We work in all areas of Central Iowa, wherever our clients take us! We take great pride in making and keeping clients happy. With each client, we go the extra distance to help reach their goals and make their transaction as stress free as possible. From first time buyers, growing families, and to empty nesters and retirees, we help our buyers and sellers work through the home selling and buying process. We work together to get houses sold as quickly as possible for top dollar and to find a new home that is perfectly suited to our client's current needs and lifestyle.  I am an accomplished business professional with 15 years of expertise in sales, marketing and business development within the commercial and residential real estate industries. A Drake University graduate, I began my real estate career in 1998 with RE/MAX Real Estate Group, went on to become the Director of Client Relations for a commercial construction company, and then the Director of Development for the Boys & Girls Clubs of Central Iowa. Additionally, I was part of the distinguished Forty under 40 Class in 2008. Lindsay is a graduate from the University of Iowa with a degree in Communication Studies. She has been part of the Julie Moore Real Estate Team for 3 years and in real estate for 4 years. Before joining the Julie Moore Real Estate Team, she facilitated mortgage closings for a company in Des Moines. Lindsay has experience in the detailed areas of pending transactions with in real estate and brings extensive knowledge to the team. We know the importance in giving back to the community and we do that in multiple ways. Our motto is “Charity shines through the windows of every home we sell.” Therefore, with each transaction completed, a donation is made to the charity of our client’s choice, as our gift to them. Since 2011, we have donated over 15,000 to many different charities on behalf of our clients. We also work hard to connect clients who have items to give away or donate to local area nonprofits during the packing and moving process. Together, we strive to make Central Iowa a better place.

Description: The Deep Capture website was created to bypass the “captured” institutions.
Full Description: The Deep Capture website was created to bypass the “captured” institutions that mediate their nation’s discourse. It was initially funded by Patrick Byrne, CEO of Overstock.com, but it is not part of Overstock. It functions as a separate, limited liability media company, whose co-owners and managers are Evren Karpak and Mark Mitchell (former partner Judd Bagley having left the organization upon returning to work at Overstock.com in 2010) . Public choice theory describes a phenomenon whereby industries take control of, or “capture”, regulators who are supposed to oversee them. The claim of this website is that powerful actors have been able to influence or take control of not just the regulators, but also law enforcement, elected officials, national media, and the intellectual establishment.
